    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="377"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.91/79</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-15">15 April,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have delayed replying to the
                        enclosed<note n="6" xml:id="d377fn6">Presumably Secretary Lansing’s letter
                        of April 2, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> because the other Powers involved seem to have virtually withdrawn from
                    their agreement to send commissioners to Syria, but in case we alone send them,
                    these letters would be just as suitable, and I am very glad to authorize you to
                    sign them.</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
